scoured the globe

00:18.151 --> 00:20.387
to find the strangest,
most exciting,

00:20.420 --> 00:23.690
most exotic acts we could find
and bring 'em here for you.

00:23.723 --> 00:27.127
This is the greatest
New York slice available.

00:27.160 --> 00:29.262
Reedus: It may be
the world's playground,

00:29.295 --> 00:31.197
but to me,
New York City is home.

00:31.231 --> 00:36.002
The most murder than
any other street in America.

00:36.036 --> 00:38.805
And I'm back, ready to catch up
with family and friends...

00:38.838 --> 00:41.441
That's Mingus.
That's my kid.

00:41.474 --> 00:43.610
...even if just for a minute.

00:43.643 --> 00:46.179
How the hell did
I end up right here?

00:46.212 --> 00:49.282
♪♪

01:10.904 --> 01:13.907
When I was a kid, my mom
took me to my first concert.

01:13.940 --> 01:16.976
♪♪

01:19.012 --> 01:21.548
It was Laurie Anderson,
and she came out

01:21.581 --> 01:23.349
in this big
glow-in-the-dark outfit

01:23.383 --> 01:24.818
with a fluorescent violin

01:24.851 --> 01:28.488
and a projection of her head
rising above her.

01:28.521 --> 01:30.990
I'd never seen
anything like it.

01:31.024 --> 01:32.725
I mean, I was 15 years old,

01:32.759 --> 01:34.594
so I hadn't seen
much of anything.

01:34.627 --> 01:36.763
But this was magical.

01:36.796 --> 01:38.164
It opened me up
to a whole new world.

01:38.198 --> 01:39.199
[Laurie Anderson's
"Sharkey Day" plays]

01:39.232 --> 01:41.935
♪ Sun's coming up ♪

01:41.968 --> 01:43.570
♪ Like a big bald head ♪

01:43.603 --> 01:46.339
♪ Poking up
over the grocery store ♪

01:48.441 --> 01:50.176
♪ It's Sharkey's day ♪

01:50.210 --> 01:52.612
It's people like Laurie
that drew me to New York.

01:52.645 --> 01:55.215
She's been part of this city's
avant-garde art scene

01:55.248 --> 01:57.217
since the '70s.

01:57.250 --> 01:59.352
When I saw her up there
in front of me,

01:59.385 --> 02:01.020
daring and fresh and real,

02:01.054 --> 02:03.656
I knew this is where I belong.

02:03.690 --> 02:06.860
