02:50.336 --> 02:52.472
-Hey!
-Hey.

02:53.473 --> 02:55.275
The hardest part
about being away

02:55.308 --> 02:56.743
is missing my son, Mingus,

02:56.776 --> 02:58.978
so any chance I get
to see him, I take it.

02:59.012 --> 03:00.613
Hey, are you close?

03:00.647 --> 03:02.682
We're meeting up here
in Washington Square Park...

03:02.715 --> 03:04.284
Okay, bye.

03:04.317 --> 03:06.619
... a place we've been
coming to together for years.

03:06.653 --> 03:07.921
Hey, man.
How 'bout a game?

03:07.954 --> 03:09.455
All right. What's up?
I'm Norman.

03:09.489 --> 03:11.357
-Cornbread, man. Please.
-Nice to meet you, man.

03:11.391 --> 03:12.692
You're second
Cornbread I've met.

03:12.725 --> 03:13.927
You play chess with him?

03:13.960 --> 03:15.295
No, but he gave me
a tattoo.

03:15.328 --> 03:16.930
Well, this time,
I'm gonna give you a whuppin'.

03:16.963 --> 03:18.364
-Oh, God. All right.
-You might win.

03:18.398 --> 03:19.499
No, I doubt it.

03:19.532 --> 03:21.000
Do you wanna play
white or black?

03:21.034 --> 03:22.635
I'll go black. That's cool.
All right. Boom.

03:22.669 --> 03:25.004
This park is famous for chess.

03:25.038 --> 03:26.706
Back in the '50s and '60s,

03:26.739 --> 03:28.942
the world's best
players came here.

03:28.975 --> 03:31.878
It's a tradition that's lived
on throughout the years.

03:31.911 --> 03:33.546
And every day,
the hustlers are here,

03:33.580 --> 03:34.948
workin' on their next move.

03:34.981 --> 03:36.849
-Check.
-Dang.

03:36.883 --> 03:38.218
You're killin' me
right now.

03:38.251 --> 03:39.586
-Check.
-Come on!

03:41.654 --> 03:44.023
Dang. Wait a minute.
You're good.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.892
Let's try one more.
Let's try one more.

03:45.925 --> 03:46.893
All right, all right.

03:46.926 --> 03:49.195
Remember envision to win.

03:50.597 --> 03:52.832
Oh-ho!

03:52.865 --> 03:54.133
Gah!

03:55.535 --> 03:57.036
Checkmate.

03:57.070 --> 03:58.871
-Not bad.
-Boom!

03:58.905 --> 04:00.907
-[Laughs]
-People see that?

04:00.940 --> 04:03.243
No, ain't nobody see that.
Nobody see that.

04:03.276 --> 04:04.744
I got my kid
comin' somewhere.

04:04.777 --> 04:06.579
I want him to play you.
When he was little,

04:06.613 --> 04:08.715
he used to come here
in this park and play chess.

04:08.748 --> 04:10.083
Did he ever
play Cornbread?

04:10.116 --> 04:11.551
I don't think so.
His name is Mingus.

04:11.584 --> 04:12.986
I don't think he ever
played you before.

04:13.019 --> 04:15.521
-Oh, I'mma beat him then.
-There he is.

04:15.555 --> 04:17.156
This is Mingus
right here, yeah.

04:17.190 --> 04:18.725
Hey, man.
Nice to meet you.

04:18.758 --> 04:20.693
Come on. Come on.

04:20.727 --> 04:22.762
I'll be honest
with you, man.

04:22.795 --> 04:25.164
I never, ever got
beaten by a kid.

04:25.198 --> 04:26.899
No. It's a lot
of pressure.

04:26.933 --> 04:28.868
Reedus: I taught Mingus
when he was young.

04:28.901 --> 04:31.237
Well, you know
how your father won?

04:31.271 --> 04:34.007
How?
He actually
envisioned the win.

04:34.040 --> 04:35.708
I see my win.

04:35.742 --> 04:37.777
It's coming up.

04:37.810 --> 04:39.779
We'd come here,
play game after game.

04:39.812 --> 04:41.180
You got it, Mingus.
Get him!

04:41.214 --> 04:43.182
And I'd watch him
beat people in minutes,

04:43.216 --> 04:46.419
and I'd think,
"That's my kid."

04:46.452 --> 04:49.522
-Is that mate?
-That was.

04:50.657 --> 04:53.259
[Cackles]
Told ya!

04:53.293 --> 04:55.295
-Thank you.
-Bye, Cornbread.

04:55.328 --> 04:56.596
Thanks, brother.
-Take care, guys.

04:56.629 --> 04:58.431
Cornbread.

04:58.464 --> 05:00.967
I was tellin' him that
you used to play here
when you were a kid.

05:01.000 --> 05:02.635
-Yeah.
-Hustle the hustlers, you know.

05:02.669 --> 05:04.370
-I still come here.
-You still play out here?

05:04.404 --> 05:05.805
Yeah. I bring
my dog to the park,

05:05.838 --> 05:07.106
and then I sit
and play chess.

05:07.140 --> 05:08.474
Oh, nice!

05:08.508 --> 05:10.243
Reedus: Seeing Mingus
in his element,

05:10.276 --> 05:12.812
I'm reminded of how great it
is that he's grown up here.

05:12.845 --> 05:14.647
So where do you take Kumo,
over here?

05:14.681 --> 05:18.151
He's got that armor you find
in every real New Yorker.

05:18.184 --> 05:19.585
We'll head this way.

05:19.619 --> 05:21.988
The biggest misconception
about New York

05:22.021 --> 05:24.324
is that New Yorkers are rude.

05:24.357 --> 05:26.826
It may come off like
we hate everybody,

05:26.859 --> 05:29.095
but it's because we live
in this [bleep] city

05:29.128 --> 05:30.330
and have everything at our --

05:30.363 --> 05:31.998
at our [bleep] whim.

05:32.031 --> 05:34.767
Because of
the intense environments

05:34.801 --> 05:36.969
that we we endure
to survive here,

05:37.003 --> 05:39.172
we're probably gonna be
the first ones

05:39.205 --> 05:41.641
to help you and not --

05:41.674 --> 05:43.776
not blink twice about it.

05:43.810 --> 05:45.478
Reedus:
Like all uncool dads,

05:45.511 --> 05:47.447
I love showin' off
my kid to my friends.

05:47.480 --> 05:48.948
All right.
We're crossin' right here.

05:48.981 --> 05:50.950
So we're headed
to meet Mario Batali

05:50.983 --> 05:52.518
before Mingus heads home,

05:52.552 --> 05:54.287
and I go on
a culinary adventure.

05:54.320 --> 05:56.356
Boom.
He's coming on his Vespa.

05:56.389 --> 05:58.925
-Yeah. His Mario Kart, actually.
-Mario Kart?

05:58.958 --> 06:00.793
You know, I'm really
good at Mario Kart.

06:00.827 --> 06:02.128
I don't know
if you know that.

06:02.161 --> 06:04.263
But I'm, like,
really good at Mario Kart.

06:04.297 --> 06:06.499
-I'm kind of amazing.
-I doubt you can beat me.

06:06.532 --> 06:08.468
-What?
-I doubt you can beat me.

06:08.501 --> 06:09.635
Are you kidding?

06:09.669 --> 06:11.337
Uh-oh.
I hear a scooter.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.639
♪♪

06:13.673 --> 06:15.675
Yeah.

06:17.043 --> 06:18.945
-What's happenin'?
-Ha-ha! How are you, brother?

06:18.978 --> 06:20.947
Your bike looks so much
bigger than my bike.

06:20.980 --> 06:23.516
How long have you been riding
a scooter in New York for?

06:23.549 --> 06:25.218
-Twelve years.
-Wow.

06:25.251 --> 06:27.019
It's so good to see you.
Good to see you.

06:27.053 --> 06:29.155
Yeah, Mario. How are you?
Do you remember Mingus?

06:29.188 --> 06:30.890
Well, not as tall as this.
You look fantastic.

06:30.923 --> 06:32.225
-Good to see you again.
-How are you?

06:32.258 --> 06:33.559
-Good.
-Everybody grows up.

06:33.593 --> 06:35.061
-We're gettin' old.
-All right.

06:35.094 --> 06:36.529
I love you.
I'll see you back at the house.

06:36.562 --> 06:37.830
-All right.
-Bye!

06:37.864 --> 06:39.999
-Have fun.
-Bye!

06:40.032 --> 06:42.368
How you been, man?
I haven't seen you in so long.

06:42.402 --> 06:44.504
I know. We've been close
to getting together.

06:44.537 --> 06:46.239
-Yeah. That's true.
-And now we're back together.

06:46.272 --> 06:48.207
It's about time.
Where are we going?

06:48.241 --> 06:49.742
We're going
to Artichoke Basille.

06:49.776 --> 06:52.011
It's my favorite
non-mine slice.

06:52.044 --> 06:53.746
-Oh, really?
-Yes. Fantastic.

06:53.780 --> 06:56.249
Reedus: Mario might be a titan
of the culinary world,

06:56.282 --> 06:57.917
but to me,
he's a friend who's always

06:57.950 --> 06:59.652
dragging me
to his favorite spots.

06:59.685 --> 07:02.388
We're off to indulge
in one my favorite things,

07:02.422 --> 07:03.623
pizza for breakfast.

07:03.656 --> 07:06.092
You're so iconic in --
in this.

07:06.125 --> 07:07.593
-Yeah.
-Everybody knows you.

07:07.627 --> 07:09.128
They say, "I can tell it
was you by your shoes."

07:09.162 --> 07:11.431
I'm like, "Really?

07:11.464 --> 07:13.866
It's the shoes
that gave me away?"

07:16.469 --> 07:19.172
We're in the heart
of Greenwich Village,

07:19.205 --> 07:20.706
a place that's long
been the center

07:20.740 --> 07:23.209
of New York's
countercultural movements.

07:23.242 --> 07:25.511
This is where
the '60s happened.

07:25.545 --> 07:28.080
It's where people question
what's going on in the world

07:28.114 --> 07:30.450
and then try to change it.

07:30.483 --> 07:31.918
That energy is contagious,

07:31.951 --> 07:34.720
and I feel it every time
I go through there.

07:34.754 --> 07:36.088
I always love this area.

07:37.457 --> 07:40.393
See the word "pizza"?
That's us.

07:40.426 --> 07:42.595
Perfect.
I'm starvin'.

07:42.628 --> 07:44.530
Battaglia: Last summer,

07:44.564 --> 07:46.599
all the hot comedians
were comin' through.

07:46.632 --> 07:48.968
You would see Jerry Seinfeld
do a 10-minute set

07:49.001 --> 07:50.470
on a Friday night
unannounced,

07:50.503 --> 07:52.238
Amy Schumer,
unannounced set.

07:52.271 --> 07:54.540
-What -- where is it?
-These three places, Cafe Wha?

07:54.574 --> 07:56.609
and then around the corner
and then the one downstairs.

07:56.642 --> 07:58.478
Wow. Very cool.

07:58.511 --> 08:00.213
I got two large comin' out.

08:00.246 --> 08:02.248
Five dollars, please.

08:04.116 --> 08:05.551
-Mario.
-How are you, my brother?

08:05.585 --> 08:07.019
-Good. How are you?
-Meet my friend, Norman.

08:07.053 --> 08:08.554
-What's up, man?
-Nice to meet you.

08:08.588 --> 08:10.256
We're gonna sit over here
and have a couple slices.

08:10.289 --> 08:11.591
Absolutely, I got a nice
hot meatball pie

08:11.624 --> 08:12.758
just came out.

08:12.792 --> 08:15.328
♪♪

08:15.361 --> 08:17.763
-This place is awesome.
-This is, in my opinion,

08:17.797 --> 08:19.665
the greatest New York
slice available.

08:19.699 --> 08:22.101
You're only sayin'
that because it's true.

08:22.134 --> 08:23.836
Exactly, exactly.

08:23.870 --> 08:25.505
Meatball slice.
All right?

08:25.538 --> 08:26.772
Yeah, this is perfect.

08:26.806 --> 08:28.474
Cheers.

08:30.376 --> 08:32.011
Mm, mm.

08:32.044 --> 08:34.146
This -- this pizza's amazing.
-Thank you very much.

08:34.180 --> 08:36.015
-You guys are genius.
-Thank you.

08:36.048 --> 08:37.216
Did you guys go to
all the comedy shows

08:37.250 --> 08:39.085
and stuff
he was tellin' me about?

08:39.118 --> 08:41.187
Sal likes to get up
there, do some improv
work once in a while.

08:41.220 --> 08:42.688
-Sal: I'm not that good.
-Really?

08:42.722 --> 08:44.524
Couple of glasses
of Tito's, he loosens up.

08:44.557 --> 08:46.626
He gets right in there.

08:46.659 --> 08:48.694
So, Mario,
this is your hood right here?

08:48.728 --> 08:50.296
Greenwich Village,
my brother,

08:50.329 --> 08:52.164
it's where I've always
lived in New York.

08:52.198 --> 08:53.699
I've been here
almost 25 years.

08:53.733 --> 08:55.868
Sal: Give me a cutter.
I made that for you.

08:55.902 --> 08:58.938
Go all over Naples,
you won't find pizza like this.

08:58.971 --> 09:01.140
Only in New York City.
-Well, you know what it is.

09:01.173 --> 09:03.276
