the nice char

09:03.309 --> 09:04.710
on those, uh,
special pans?

09:04.744 --> 09:06.712
That's the story.
-Yup.

09:06.746 --> 09:08.314
So how do you get
the char on the pan?

09:08.347 --> 09:09.949
You don't wash 'em.

09:09.982 --> 09:11.551
-Don't wash 'em?
-They're washed.

09:11.584 --> 09:14.120
They're just not
scraped off fine and clean.

09:14.153 --> 09:16.522
Careful. That is hot as balls.
-Hot as balls.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.724
You're gonna have to let
those balls rest, young man.

09:18.758 --> 09:20.159
I know we're in
the West Village,

09:20.192 --> 09:21.561
but those balls
have to rest.

09:21.594 --> 09:23.162
Have to rest.

09:23.195 --> 09:25.298
Can we get two more of those,
Randall, please?

09:25.331 --> 09:27.500
What's it like running
restaurants in New York?

09:27.533 --> 09:29.869
Do you have certain areas

09:29.902 --> 09:31.871
where certain restaurant
types go, or --

09:31.904 --> 09:34.307
Although we have Babbo,
Lupa and OTTO

09:34.340 --> 09:36.208
all within
four-block range,

09:36.242 --> 09:38.010
they're each
different niches.

09:38.044 --> 09:40.179
They're different experiences.
It's not the same menu.

09:40.212 --> 09:41.581
OTTO used to be
where they had

09:41.614 --> 09:43.316
the Saturday Night Live
after-party.

09:43.349 --> 09:45.651
Oh, wow.
It was called
One Fifth at that time.

09:45.685 --> 09:48.754
♪♪

09:50.556 --> 09:53.259
And every Sunday,
Andy Warhol had brunch in there.

09:53.292 --> 09:54.694
What?

09:54.727 --> 09:57.096
So you could only
imagine the intermingling

09:57.129 --> 10:01.000
and magnificence of the DNA
in my walls at that restaurant.

10:01.033 --> 10:03.936
Dude. Did you ever
meet John Belushi?

10:03.970 --> 10:05.371
-Yeah, of course.
-Really?

10:05.404 --> 10:07.039
